TITLE: Optimized Accessor Update with updateTriggers (React/TSX)
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the optimal way to handle accessor updates based on props in React using `updateTriggers`. The original `DATA` is passed to `ScatterplotLayer`, and `updateTriggers: { getRadius: year }` ensures only the radius calculation is redone when `year` changes, maximizing performance.
SOURCE: https://github.com/visgl/deck.gl/blob/master/docs/developer-guide/performance.md#_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
function App({year}: {
  year: number;
}) {
  const layers = [
    new ScatterplotLayer<CensusTract>({
      // `data` never changes
      data: DATA,
      getPosition: (d: CensusTract) => d.centroid,
      // radius depends on `year`
      getRadius: (d: CensusTract) => Math.sqrt(d.populationsByYear[year]),
      updateTriggers: {
        // This tells deck.gl to recalculate radius when `year` changes
        getRadius: year
      }
    })
  ];

  return <DeckGL
    // ...
    layers={layers}
  />;
}
```

