TITLE: Creating and Adding ScatterplotLayer with Mapbox - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to create a `MapboxLayer` instance and add it to a Mapbox map. It uses a `ScatterplotLayer` from deck.gl to visualize data on the map. It waits for the map to load before adding the layer, ensuring the map is ready.  The example includes setting layer properties such as ID, type, data, and visual attributes (e.g., position, radius, color).
