TITLE: Optimized Accessor Update with updateTriggers (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates the efficient use of `updateTriggers` in deck.gl. Instead of remapping the data, the original `DATA` is passed, and `updateTriggers: { getRadius: year }` tells the layer to only recalculate the radius when the `year` prop changes, significantly improving performance.
SOURCE: https://github.com/visgl/deck.gl/blob/master/docs/developer-guide/performance.md#_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
function render(year: number) {
  const layers = [
    new ScatterplotLayer<CensusTract>({
      // `data` never changes
      data: DATA,
      getPosition: (d: CensusTract) => d.centroid,
      // radius depends on `year`
      getRadius: (d: CensusTract) => Math.sqrt(d.populationsByYear[year]),
      updateTriggers: {
        // This tells deck.gl to recalculate radius when `year` changes
        getRadius: year
      }
    })
  ];

  deckInstance.setProps({layers});
}
```

