TITLE: Efficient Layer Visibility Toggle - TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This TypeScript code implements an efficient approach for toggling layer visibility in deck.gl. It uses the `visible` prop to show or hide layers without removing them from the scene. The layers' internal states are retained in memory, allowing for instant re-rendering when visibility is toggled back on.
SOURCE: https://github.com/visgl/deck.gl/blob/master/docs/developer-guide/performance.md#_snippet_22

LANGUAGE: ts
CODE:
```
function render(layerVisibility: {
  circles: boolean;
  labels: boolean;
}) {
  const layers = [
    // when visibility is off, this layer's internal states will be retained in memory, making turning it back on instant
    new ScatterplotLayer({
      id: 'circles',
      visible: layerVisibility.circles,
      // ...
    }),
    new TextLayer({
      id: 'labels',
      visible: layerVisibility.labels,
      // ...
    })
  ];

  deckInstance.setProps({layers});
}
```

