TITLE: Generating Attributes in Web Worker
DESCRIPTION: This TypeScript code snippet shows how to prepare attributes for a `PointCloudLayer` within a web worker. It flattens the position and color data from `POINT_CLOUD_DATA` into typed arrays suitable for direct use by the GPU. The worker then sends the processed data back to the main thread via `postMessage`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/visgl/deck.gl/blob/master/docs/developer-guide/performance.md#_snippet_38

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
// positions can be sent as either float32 or float64, depending on precision requirements
// point[0].x, point[0].y, point[0].z, point[1].x, point[1].y, point[1].z, ...
const positions = new Float64Array(POINT_CLOUD_DATA.flatMap((d: DataType) => d.position));
// point[0].r, point[0].g, point[0].b, point[1].r, point[1].g, point[1].b, ...
const colors = new Uint8Array(POINT_CLOUD_DATA.flatMap((d: DataType) => d.color));

// send back to main thread
postMessage({pointCount: POINT_CLOUD_DATA.length, positions, colors}, [positions.buffer, colors.buffer]);
```

