TITLE: Use deck.gl with CARTO data source query to visualize data with GeoJsonLayer
DESCRIPTION: This example illustrates fetching data directly using the CARTO SQL API through the query function, then transforming and visualizing this data with a GeoJsonLayer in deck.gl. It requires configuring accessToken, connectionName, and SQL query parameters. The layer visually represents geospatial points with positions and radii, enabling detailed spatial analysis. Dependencies include '@deck.gl/react', '@deck.gl/layers', and '@deck.gl/carto'.
