TITLE: Using Binary Data for ScatterplotLayer with target (Efficient)
DESCRIPTION: This optimized version uses the `target` argument in the accessors. By modifying the existing `target` array directly, it further reduces object creation. This approach offers the highest performance, especially for animation and frequent updates.  It utilizes the `target` array to avoid allocations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/visgl/deck.gl/blob/master/docs/developer-guide/performance.md#_snippet_36

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
const DATA = {src: binaryData, length: binaryData.length / 6}

const layer = new ScatterplotLayer({
  data: DATA,
  getPosition: (_, {index, data, target}) => {
    target[0] = data.src[index * 6];
    target[1] = data.src[index * 6 + 1];
    target[2] = 0;
    return target;
  },
  getRadius: (_, {index, data}) => {
    return data.src[index * 6 + 2];
  },
  getFillColor: (_, {index, data, target}) => {
    target[0] = data.src[index * 6 + 3];
    target[1] = data.src[index * 6 + 4];
    target[2] = data.src[index * 6 + 5];
    target[3] = 255;
    return target;
  }
})
```

