DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates setting up a `HexagonLayer` in JavaScript, fetching data asynchronously, and configuring a transition for the `elevationScale` prop to make the hexagons "grow" when data loads. Requires `@deck.gl/core` and `@deck.gl/aggregation-layers`. The `transitions` object specifies the `elevationScale` prop should animate over 3000ms.
SOURCE: https://github.com/visgl/deck.gl/blob/master/docs/developer-guide/animations-and-transitions.md#_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import {Deck} from '@deck.gl/core';
import {HexagonLayer} from '@deck.gl/aggregation-layers';

const deckInstance = new Deck({
  // ...
  layer: getLayers(null)
});

const resp = await fetch('/path/to/data.json');
const data = await resp.json();
deckInstance.setProps({
  layer: getLayers(data)
});

function getLayers(data) {
  return [
    new HexagonLayer({
      id: '3d-heatmap',
      data,
      getPosition: d => [d.longitude, d.latitude],
      getElevationWeight: d => d.count,
      extruded: true,
      elevationScale: data && data.length ? 50 : 0,
      transitions: {
        elevationScale: 3000
      }
    })
  ];
}
```

