TITLE: Interleaved Attributes in Web Worker
DESCRIPTION: This TypeScript code shows how to create interleaved attributes within a web worker.  It combines position and color data into a single `Float32Array`, which is then sent back to the main thread.  The colors are normalized when sent as floats.
SOURCE: https://github.com/visgl/deck.gl/blob/master/docs/developer-guide/performance.md#_snippet_40

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
// x0,y0,z0, r0,g0,b0, x1,y1,z1, r1,g1,b1, ...
const positionsAndColors = new Float32Array(POINT_CLOUD_DATA.flatMap(d => [
  d.position[0],
  d.position[1],
  d.position[2],
  // colors must be normalized if sent as floats
  d.color[0] / 255,
  d.color[1] / 255,
  d.color[2] / 255
]));

// send back to main thread
postMessage({pointCount: POINT_CLOUD_DATA.length, positionsAndColors}, [positionsAndColors.buffer]);
```

