TITLE: Implementing React Mercator Controller Wrapper - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Implements a React component that wraps an ES6 MercatorControllerState instance. It uses an EventManager to register DOM event handlers on a rendered element (implied by the component context). Event handlers like _onDragStart call corresponding methods on the controllerState instance to calculate new viewport states, which are then presumably propagated via the onChangeViewport callback. The component includes toggles for various interactive features and properties to indicate hover and drag states.
