TITLE: Defining accessor functions for TextLayer properties in deck.gl (JavaScript/TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: Provides optional accessor functions for retrieving text content, position, size, color, angle, text anchor, alignment, pixel offset, background color, border color, and border width. Each accessor has a default value and can be customized per object.
SOURCE: https://github.com/visgl/deck.gl/blob/master/docs/api-reference/layers/text-layer.md#_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
#### `getText` (Accessor&lt;string&gt;) {#gettext}

* Default: `x => x.text`

Method called to retrieve the content of each text label.

#### `getPosition` (Accessor&lt;Position&gt;) ![transition-enabled](https://img.shields.io/badge/transition-enabled-green.svg?style=flat-square") {#getposition}

* Default: `x => x.position`

Method called to retrieve the location of each text label.

#### `getSize` (Accessor&lt;number&gt;) ![transition-enabled](https://img.shields.io/badge/transition-enabled-green.svg?style=flat-square") {#getsize}

* Default: `32`

The font size of each text label, in units specified by `sizeUnits` (default pixels).
* If a number is provided, it is used as the size for all objects.
* If a function is provided, it is called on each object to retrieve its size.

#### `getColor` (Accessor&lt;Color&gt;) ![transition-enabled](https://img.shields.io/badge/transition-enabled-green.svg?style=flat-square") {#getcolor}

* Default: `[0, 0, 0, 255]`

The rgba color is in the format of `[r, g, b, [a]]`. Each channel is a number between 0-255 and `a` is 255 if not supplied.
* If an array is provided, it is used as the color for all objects.
* If a function is provided, it is called on each object to retrieve its color.

#### `getAngle` (Accessor&lt;number&gt;) ![transition-enabled](https://img.shields.io/badge/transition-enabled-green.svg?style=flat-square") {#getangle}

* Default: `0`

The rotating angle of each text label, in degrees.
* If a number is provided, it is used as the angle for all objects.
* If a function is provided, it is called on each object to retrieve its angle.

#### `getTextAnchor` (Accessor&lt;string&gt;) {#gettextanchor}

* Default: `'middle'`

The text anchor. Options include `'start'`, `'middle'`, `'end'`.
* If a string is provided, it is used as the text anchor for all objects.
* If a function is provided, it is called on each object to retrieve its text anchor.

#### `getAlignmentBaseline` (Accessor&lt;string&gt;) {#getalignmentbaseline}

* Default: `'center'`

The alignment baseline, options `'top'`, `'center'`, `'bottom'`.
* If a string is provided, it is used as the alignment baseline for all objects.
* If a function is provided, it is called on each object to retrieve its alignment baseline.

#### `getPixelOffset` (Accessor&lt;number[2]&gt;) ![transition-enabled](https://img.shields.io/badge/transition-enabled-green.svg?style=flat-square") {#getpixeloffset}

* Default: `[0, 0]`

Screen space offset relative to the `coordinates` in pixel units.
* If an array is provided, it is used as the offset for all objects.
* If a function is provided, it is called on each object to retrieve its offset.

#### `getBackgroundColor` (Accessor&lt;Color&gt;) ![transition-enabled](https://img.shields.io/badge/transition-enabled-green.svg?style=flat-square") {#getbackgroundcolor}

* Default: `[255, 255, 255, 255]`

The background color, effective if `background: true`.
* The color format `[r, g, b, [a]]` with channels 0-255.
* Can be an array (applied to all) or a function (per object).

#### `getBorderColor` (Accessor&lt;Color&gt;) ![transition-enabled](https://img.shields.io/badge/transition-enabled-green.svg?style=flat-square") {#getbordercolor}

* Default: `[0, 0, 0, 255]`

The border color of the background, effective if `background: true`.
* Format similar to background color.

#### `getBorderWidth` (Accessor&lt;number&gt;) ![transition-enabled](https://img.shields.io/badge/transition-enabled-green.svg?style=flat-square") {#getborderwidth}

* Default: `0`

The border thickness for each text label in pixels, effective if `background: true`.
* Can be a number or a function returning the thickness.
```

