TITLE: Defining Custom Median Operation in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet showcases a custom aggregation operation to calculate the median. It takes an array of point indices and a function to retrieve values. The values are retrieved using `getValue` and sorted. The median is then computed by accessing the middle element or the average of the two middle elements in case of an even number of values and it requires the `pointIndices` and `getValue` as input.
SOURCE: https://github.com/visgl/deck.gl/blob/master/docs/api-reference/aggregation-layers/cpu-aggregator.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
function median(pointIndices: number[], getValue: (index: number) => number) {
  const values = pointIndices.map(getValue);
  values.sort((a, b) => a - b);
  return values[values.length >> 1];
}

aggregator.setProps({
  customOperations: [null, median, null]
});
```

