TITLE: Updating Layers with Deck.setProps in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript code snippet demonstrates how to update deck.gl layers by creating a new Deck instance and updating its props with new layer instances.  It uses `ScatterplotLayer` and `TextLayer` to display flight data fetched from a hypothetical server. The `update` function is called repeatedly using `setTimeout` to simulate real-time data updates.
SOURCE: https://github.com/visgl/deck.gl/blob/master/docs/developer-guide/using-layers.md#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import {Deck} from '@deck.gl/core';
import {ScatterplotLayer, TextLayer} from '@deck.gl/layers';

const deckInstance = new Deck({
  initialViewState: {
    longitude: -122.4,
    latitude: 37.8,
    zoom: 8
  },
  controller: true
});

update();

async function update() {
  // `queryServer` is a hypothetical function that contacts a server to fetch a list of flight locations
  // in the shape of [{lon: -122.39, lat: 37.62, alt: 1800, callSign: 'SKW 3342'}, ...]
  const flights = await queryServer({time: Date.now()});

  deckInstance.setProps({
    layers: [
      new ScatterplotLayer({
        id: 'circles',
        data: flights,
        getPosition: d => [d.lng, d.lat, d.alt],
        getFillColor: [255, 0, 0],
        getRadius: 3,
        radiusUnits: 'pixels'
      }),
      new TextLayer({
        id: 'labels',
        data: flights,
        getText: d => d.callSign,
        getPosition: d => [d.lon, d.lat, d.alt],
        getSize: 12
      })
    ]
  });

  // refresh again after 60 seconds
  setTimeout(update, 60000);
}
```

