TITLE: Configuring TextLayer Font Atlas Settings in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript snippet demonstrates how to use the proposed `fontSettings` prop within a deck.gl `TextLayer` instance. It shows how to configure options for both standard and Signed Distance Field (SDF) font atlas generation, including `fontSize`, `buffer`, `sdf`, `radius`, and `cutoff`. These settings influence the shared font atlas texture but do not directly affect the rendered size of individual text labels.
SOURCE: https://github.com/visgl/deck.gl/blob/master/dev-docs/RFCs/v6.3/text-layer-font-setting-api.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import {TextLayer} from '@deck.gl/layers'

const textLayer = new TextLayer({
  ...,
  characterSet: 'abcdefg',
  fontFamily: 'Monaco, monospace',
  fontWeight: 'normal',

  fontSettings: {
    // shared options between non-sdf and sdf
    // this fontSize if only applied for generating fontAtlas
    // it does not impact the size of the text labels 
    fontSize: 64, 
    // Whitespace buffer around each side of the character
    buffer: 2,

    // `sdf` only options
    // https://github.com/mapbox/tiny-sdf
    sdf: true,
    // if `sdf` is false, the following parameters are not appliable
