TITLE: Providing a getPickingInfo Callback for Non-Iterable Binary Data in ScatterplotLayer - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates specifying a `getPickingInfo` callback to reconstruct a valid `object` for picking events when `data` is a non-iterable binary object. This function uses the index to access the binary buffer, populating the picked object's position, radius, and color via subarrays. It ensures interactivity features like picking correctly interpret binary data representations in deck.gl layers.
SOURCE: https://github.com/visgl/deck.gl/blob/master/dev-docs/RFCs/v7.2/binary-data-rfc.md#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
new ScatterplotLayer({
  ...
  getPickingInfo: ({info, data}) => {
    const i = info.index * 6;
    info.object = {
      position: data.src.subarray(i, i + 2),
      radius: data.src[i + 2],
      color: data.src.subarray(i + 3, i + 6)
    };
    return info;
  }
})
```

