TITLE: Animation Class Constructor and Methods - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet describes the methods available for the Animation class.  The constructor initializes the animation. The `to()` method adds a keyframe to the animation with a value, time, and optional easing function.  The `loop()` method enables the animation to restart when finished. The `evaluate()` method returns the current state of the animation.  The `isDone()` method returns if the animation is complete.
