TITLE: Using Binary Data for ScatterplotLayer (Inefficient)
DESCRIPTION: This code constructs a `ScatterplotLayer` using data unpacked from a `Float32Array`. The data is first converted into a JavaScript array, which consumes significant CPU time and memory, particularly for large datasets.  It illustrates inefficient data handling and the creation of intermediate data structures.
SOURCE: https://github.com/visgl/deck.gl/blob/master/docs/developer-guide/performance.md#_snippet_34

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
type DataType = {
  position: [lon: number, lat: number];
  radius: number;
  color: [r: number, g: numer, b: number];
}
const data: DataType[] = [];
for (let i = 0; i < binaryData.length; i += 6) {
  data.push({
    position: [binaryData[i], binaryData[i + 1]],
    radius: binaryData[i + 2],
    color: [binaryData[i + 3], binaryData[i + 4], binaryData[i + 5]]
  });
}

const data = new ScatterplotLayer<DataType>{
  data,
  getPosition: (d: DataType) => d.position,
  getRadius: (d: DataType) => d.radius,
  getFillColor: (d: DataType) => d.color
});
```

