TITLE: Maximum Weight Calculation Fragment Shader
DESCRIPTION: GLSL fragment shader that samples the aggregation texture to calculate total counts, total weights, and maximum weights. It outputs these values to different color channels to be used for later rendering.
SOURCE: https://github.com/visgl/deck.gl/blob/master/dev-docs/RFCs/v6.0/gpu-screengrid-aggregation-rfc.md#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: glsl
CODE:
```
varying vec2 vTextureCoord;
uniform sampler2D uSampler;

void main(void) {
  vec4 textureColor = texture2D(uSampler, vec2(vTextureCoord.s, vTextureCoord.t));
  // Red: total count, Green: total weight, Alpha: maximum weight
  gl_FragColor = vec4(textureColor.r, textureColor.g, 0., textureColor.g);
}
```

