TITLE: Defining a Custom Picking Color Attribute in a deck.gl Layer (JS)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to define a custom attribute named `customPickingColors` within a deck.gl layer's `initializeState` method using the `AttributeManager`. This attribute will store the unique picking color for each object's vertices, enabling GPU-based picking. It uses `GL.UNSIGNED_BYTE` for the type, suitable for storing 3-byte color values.
SOURCE: https://github.com/visgl/deck.gl/blob/master/docs/developer-guide/custom-layers/picking.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import GL from '@luma.gl/constants';

class MyLayer extends Layer {
  initializeState() {
    this.state.attributeManager.add({
      customPickingColors: {
        size: 3,
        type: GL.UNSIGNED_BYTE,
        update: this.calculatePickingColors
      }
    });
  }
}
```

