TITLE: Installing Dependencies on MacOS Apple Silicon (M1) with Homebrew
DESCRIPTION: Commands to install native arm64 dependencies for MacOS on Apple Silicon by using the 'arch -arm64' prefix with Homebrew, and configuring Python environment by installing Python via Homebrew and symlinking it for use in the build process.
SOURCE: https://github.com/visgl/deck.gl/blob/master/docs/contributing.md#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
arch -arm64 brew install pkg-config cairo pango libpng jpeg giflib librsvg

# Ensure Python is installed
brew install python
sudo ln -s /opt/homebrew/bin/python3 /opt/homebrew/bin/python

# Run bootstrap with Python environment
CPLUS_INCLUDE_PATH=/opt/homebrew/include yarn bootstrap
```

